ular), but I included the excerpted paragraph as a reminder that these are =
hard questions.

What does seem clear to me is that the way to answer hard questions is to n=
ot seek to freeze technology in time but rather to consider how many regula=
tory obsessions =E2=80=94 including Windows dominance =E2=80=94 are ultimat=
ely addressed by technology getting better, not by regulators treating mist=
aken assumptions (like operating system openness being an unalloyed good) a=
s unchangeable grounds for competition.

